Subject: RE: [T2] engine removal/supporting tranny

On Wed, 17 Apr 2002, Ian Janes wrote:

> When I remove type4 motors its been easier to drop the tranny with the motor
> and pull them both out,, it is a big pain in the ass to try and get it all
> lined up when you just remove the motor  it is much easier to put it back in
> with the tranny attached.

maybe with a manual tranny. But with an Automatic it is not neccesary to
pull the engine back as far since there is no rear driveshaft to clear

Bob

